  "description": "Sutton Hospital, The Charterhouse (various locations - see plan)\r\n\r\n(T15) Fig - Undertake crown reduction by circa 3 metres and prune to provide 2 metre clearance from building and pathway. Pruning cuts should observe pruning points and retain the main branch structure.\r\n\r\n(T12) Cherry - Crown lift to 3 metres above ground level. Remove all deadwood in excess of 25mm in diameter.\r\n\r\n(T9) Apple - Prune to reduce overall crown dimensions by circa 2 metres, pruning back to previous pruning points. Prune to provide 1 metre clearance from adjoining wires. Crown lift to provide 3 metres height clearance.\r\n\r\n(T1) Pride of India - Remove all deadwood in excess of 25mm in diameter.\r\n\r\n(T2) London plane - Reduce southerly crown extent by circa 4 metres pruning to suitable side branches. Prune to provide 6 metres clearance from building but respecting main branches and retaining those. Shorten branch extending towards Wild Service tree by circa 2 metres to allow the Service Tree to develop more fully.",
